RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUTTONWOOD TREE broke alertly and was hustled to establish the early lead, was well handled through the backstretch run while setting decent fractions, drew to a clear lead approaching the top of the lane, drew off in the stretch run, kept to task while a bit green in the final stages and remained clear to the wire. START THEM UP tracked the decent early pace, was well positioned through the backstretch run, raced two then three wide along the second turn, could not keep pace with BUTTONWOOD TREE in upper stretch, drifted in a bit and bumped COOPERKLIMT at mid-stretch, battled that rival for second into deep stretch and won the nod on the wire for place. COOPERKLIMT settled in the second flight, raced two wide into the backstretch run, slipped to the rail heading to the far turn, gained ground at the quarter marker, could not keep pace with BUTTONWOOD TREE in the drive, was bumped by START THEM UP and came in a bit tight at the furlong pole, battled START THEM UP to the wire for second and just missed for that position, while clear in the end for third. LIBERTY WOLF stalked the decent pace, lost ground to BUTTONWOOD TREE on the second turn and weakened in the stretch. STRAMA took back off of the decent early pace, maintained a three wide path to the second turn and did not factor in the drive. FANTASTIC DREAM hopped leaving the start and was off a step slowly, settled off of the pace while saving ground and did not threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONTRARY CHIEFTAIN hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered to settle off of the moderate early pace while saving ground, improved position along the backstretch run, was roused heading into the far turn, came in a bit tight at the quarter marker and jostled his stablemate while attempting to split rivals, tipped two wide for the drive, loomed at the furlong pole, overtook STOUT approaching the sixteenth-marker and held in a drive in the final stages to prove best. STOUT prominent in the early stages, assumed command along the first turn and set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, showed the way to the quarter marker, raced in hand into upper stretch, came under pressure nearing the furlong pole, could not hold off CONTRARY CHIEFTAIN in the late stages and was outfinished, while holding for second. SILENT BULLET allowed to settle in the early running, advanced to be well placed through the backstretch run, gained ground on the second turn, was floated out a bit nearing the quarter marker and came four wide into the stretch, was outkicked in the drive and was well clear in the end for third. FINE SOFT MORNING forwardly placed in the early running, drifted out along the first turn, recovered into the backstretch run and attended to the moderate pace to the second turn, came in tight and was jostled a bit by CONTRARY CHIEFTAIN heading to the quarter marker, dropped back in upper stretch and tired in the drive.

LASSIE CAT unhurried in the early stages, was roused four wide into the stretch, rallied in the drive, could not reel in the winner in deep stretch and bested the rest. TWO TWELVE hustled to establish the early lead, showed speed into the turn, set solid fractions while on a clear lead to the quarter marker, was set down at mid-stretch, weakened nearing the sixteenth-pole and was overtaken by HANNAH IN A HURRY, was outfinished for second in deep stretch and held safely for third. CRY ME A RUNNER chased the fast early pace, gained ground two wide on the turn, ran evenly to the furlong marker and gave way in the late stages. BLURSDAY forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the fast pace while three deep into the turn, could not keep pace in upper stretch and tired in the drive.
